doc.ContractDescription: IGF::CT::IGF JANITORIAL SERVICES FOR THE FEDERAL REGIONAL CENTER (FRC) BLDG A, IN MAYNARD, MA EXERCISING OPTION I. PERIOD OF PERFORMANCE 6/1/2016 TO 5/31/2017

NRI SMALL, A NOVEL POWERED LEG PROSTHESIS SIMULATOR FOR SENSING AND CONTROL DEVELOPMENT ROBOTIC LEG PROSTHESES HAVE RECENTLY BEEN DEVELOPED IN AN EFFORT TO RESTORE NATURAL GAIT IN AMPUTEES. FURTHER RESEARCH IS REQUIRED TO ALLOW THESE DEVICES TO PRODUCE ADAPTIVE AND BIOMIMETIC BEHAVIORS ACROSS DIFFERENT WALKING SPEEDS AND TERRAINS. HERE WE PROPOSE TO BUILD A LEG PROSTHESIS SIMULATOR TO EFFECTIVELY SEARCH THE SPACE OF POTENTIAL CONTROL AND SENSING STRATEGIES TO FIND THE BEST MEANS TO IMPROVE AMPUTEE LOCOMOTION THROUGH WEARABLE ELECTROMECHANICAL TECHNOLOGY. USING A CABLE DRIVE MECHANISM, THE PROPOSED LEG PROSTHESIS SIMULATOR WILL USE OFF BOARD POWER, ACTUATION AND CONTROL HARDWARE TO APPLY TORQUE TO BOTH PROSTHETIC AND RESIDUAL LIMB JOINTS WHILE AN AMPUTEE PARTICIPANT WALKS ON AN INSTRUMENTED TREADMILL. THE APPLIED TORQUE PROFILES WILL BE DETERMINED FROM A NEUROMUSCULAR MODEL BASED CONTROL PARADIGM. THE NEUROMUSCULAR MODEL WILL INCLUDE OPTIMIZED MUSCLE TENDON PARAMETERS AS WELL AS A REFLEXIVE FEEDBACK BASED CONTROL SCHEME FOR EACH MUSCLE. FOR A GIVEN AMPUTEE TEST PARTICIPANT, THE MODEL WILL BE TUNED TO MATCH THE PARAMETERS DERIVED FROM A HEIGHT AND WEIGHT MATCHED PERSON WITHOUT AMPUTATION. THE PROPOSED RESEARCH PROGRAM SHALL INCLUDE TWO PHASES. IN A FIRST PHASE, 2.5 YEARS, WE PROPOSE TO DESIGN AND FABRICATE THE TRANSTIBIAL PROSTHESIS SIMULATOR APPARATUS, PROGRAM THE MODEL BASED CONTROL AND SENSING PARADIGMS, AND CLINICALLY EVALUATE THESE PARADIGMS ON WALKING TRANSTIBIAL AMPUTEES THROUGH BIOMECHANICAL AND PHYSIOLOGICAL MEASURES. IN A SECOND PHASE, 2.5 YEARS, WE PROPOSE TO DESIGN AND FABRICATE THE TRANSFEMORAL PROSTHESIS SIMULATOR APPARATUS, PROGRAM THE MODEL BASED CONTROL AND SENSING PARADIGMS, AND EVALUATE THESE PARADIGMS ON WALKING TRANSFEMORAL AMPUTEES THROUGH BIOMECHANICAL AND HYSIOLOGICAL MEASURES.
